'''Oğuz Aydın''' ({{IPA|tr|oˈuz ajˈdɯn|lang}}; born 27 October 2000) is a Turkish professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[winger (association football)|winger]] for [[Fenerbahçe S.K. (football)|Fenerbahçe]]. Born in the Netherlands as '''Redur Kaya''' ({{IPA|tr|ɾeˈduɾ kaˈja|}}), he represents the [[Turkey national football team|Turkey national team]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.azfanpage.nl/selecties-jeugdelftallen-2013-2014/|title=Selecties jeugdelftallen 2013-2014|date=June 5, 2013|website=www.azfanpage.nl}}</ref>

==Club career==
===Early career===
Aydın began his career with [[AZ Alkmaar]] in 2011, before moving to Turkey in 2016. He played for [[Bucaspor|Bucaspor Academy]] from 2016 to 2017 season to January 2018.

Aydın began his senior career with [[Bucaspor]] in January 2018, and moved to [[Bucaspor 1928]] on 7 August 2019. He spent first half of the 2019-20 season on loan with [[Karacabey Belediyespor]], then he back to Bucaspor 1928 for the second half of the 2019-20 season.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hurriyet.com.tr/sporarena/oguz-aydin-kimdir-nereli-kac-yasinda-oguz-aydin-hangi-takimlarda-forma-giydi-42602327|title=Oğuz Aydın kimdir? İşte futbol kariyer bilgileri|date=October 24, 2024|website=Hürriyet}}</ref>

In his second season, he emerged as a versatile player for Bucaspor 1928, occupying multiple positions, in the first eleven, mainly at both winger positions. He finished the season with 11 goals and 3 assists across all competitions.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sabah.com.tr/izmir/2021/06/08/bucasporun-genc-golcusu-oguz-aydin-alanyaspora|title=Bucaspor'un genç golcüsü Oğuz Aydın, Alanyaspor'a|date=June 8, 2021|website=Sabah}}</ref>

===Alanyaspor===
On 24 June 2021, he transferred to [[Alanyaspor]], signing a 5-year contract.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.haberturk.com/oguz-aydin-alanyasporda-3114078-spor|title=Oğuz Aydın Alanyaspor'da|date=June 24, 2021|website=haberturk.com}}</ref> He made his professional debut with Alanyaspor in a 6–3 [[Süper Lig]] win over [[Kayserispor]] on 18 October 2021.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2021/10/18/turkey/super-lig/alanyaspor/kayserispor/3556989/|title=Alanyaspor vs. Kayserispor - 18 October 2021 - Soccerway|website=int.soccerway.com}}</ref>

He showed a very successful performance in his club with 13 goals in 77 matches in all competitions, where he stayed for 3 seasons, and was promoted to the [[Turkey national football team|national team]].

===Fenerbahçe===
On 16 July 2024, Aydın transferred to [[Fenerbahçe S.K. (football)|Fenerbahçe]] with a 4-year agreement.<ref>{{Cite news |title=Ailemize hoş geldin Oğuz Aydın|publisher=Fenerbahçe SK|url=https://www.fenerbahce.org/haberler/futbol/2024/7/ailemize-hos-geldin-oguz-aydin|date=15 July 2024|access-date=6 February 2025}}</ref> He made his continental debut in a 1–2 [[UEFA Champions League]] [[2024–25 UEFA Champions League#Qualifying rounds|2024-25 third qualifying round]] lose against [[Lille OSC|Lille]] in [[France]] on 6 August 2024.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Fenerbahçe SK|url=https://www.fenerbahce.org/haberler/futbol/2024/8/losc-lille-2-1-fenerbahce|title=LOSC Lille 2-1 Fenerbahçe|date=6 August 2024|access-date=6 August 2024}}</ref>

On 10 August 2024, he made his Süper Lig debut in a 1–0 home win against [[Adana Demirspor]] in [[Şükrü Saraçoğlu Stadium]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Fenerbahçe SK|url=https://www.fenerbahce.org/haberler/futbol/2024/8/fenerbahcemiz-lige-adana-demirspor-galibiyetiyle-basladi|title=Fenerbahçemiz lige Adana Demirspor galibiyetiyle başladı|date=10 August 2024|access-date=17 March 2025}}</ref>

On 23 November 2024, in an away match against [[Kayserispor]], Aydın wore his first cap as a starter and scored 2 goals in 11 minutes.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=NtvSpor|url=https://www.ntvspor.net/futbol/oguz-aydin-hoca-sansi-verdi-elimden-geleni-yaptim-6741f4eb12dd4303efdb2e82|title=Hoca şans verdi, elimden geleni yaptım|date=24 November 2024|access-date=25 November 2024}}</ref> One week later, on 2 December 2024, he scored an early goal at 2nd minute of the match and helped in an 3–1 [[Süper Lig]] victory against [[Gaziantep FK]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Fenerbahçe SK|url=https://fenerbahce.org/haberler/futbol/2024/12/fenerbahce-3-1-gaziantep-fk|title=Fenerbahçe 3-1 Gaziantep FK|date=2 December 2024|access-date=3 December 2024}}</ref>

On 5 February 2025, he made a 61st mins substitute in a [[Turkish Cup]] match against [[Erzurumspor]] and performed three assist in 78th, 81st and 89th mins.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Fenerbahçe SK|url=https://www.fenerbahce.org/haberler/futbol/2025/2/fenerbahce-5-0-erzurumspor-fk|title=Fenerbahçe 5-0 Erzurumspor FK|date=5 February 2025|access-date=6 February 2025}}</ref>

==International career==
Born in the Netherlands. He represented the [[Turkey national under-19 football team|Turkey U19]]s in a 1–1 [[2019 UEFA European Under-19 Championship]] tie with the [[Denmark national under-19 football team|Denmark U19]]s on 24 March 2018.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=TFF.org|url=https://www.tff.org/default.aspx?pageID=274&ftxtID=28948&1337pg=41|title=U19 Milliler, Elit Tur ikinci maçında Danimarka ile 1-1 berabere kaldı|date=24 March 2018|access-date=3 December 2024}}</ref> On 25 March 2022, he represented [[Turkey national under-21 football team|Turkey U21]]s in a 0–2 [[2023 UEFA European Under-21 Championship qualification]] away win over the [[Scotland national under-21 football team|Scotland U21]]s.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=TFF.org|url=https://www.tff.org/Default.aspx?pageId=200&ftxtId=37310|title=Ümit Milli Takım, İskoçya'yı 2-0 yendi|date=26 March 2022|access-date=3 December 2024}}</ref>

In March 2024 Aydın received his first call-up to the senior [[Turkey national football team|Turkey squad]] for the match against [[Hungary national football team|Hungary]] and [[Austria national football team|Austria]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Yeni Asır|url=https://www.yeniasir.com.tr/spor/bucaspor/2024/03/22/bucasporda-oguz-gururu|title=Bucaspor'da Oğuz Gururu|date=22 March 2024|access-date=3 December 2024}}</ref> Aydın made his debut for the [[Turkey national football team|Turkey national team]] on 4 June 2024 in a friendly against [[Italy national football team|Italy]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=ESPN|url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/match/_/gameId/698879/turkey-italy|title=Italy v Turkey game report|date=4 June 2024|access-date=4 June 2024}}</ref>

Having made a successful start to the [[2024–25 Fenerbahçe S.K. season|2024–25]] season with [[Fenerbahçe S.K. (football)|Fenerbahçe]], Aydın was called up by [[Vincenzo Montella]] to the [[Turkey national football team|national team]] for the [[2024–25 UEFA Nations League promotion/relegation play-offs#League A vs League B|2024–25 UEFA Nations League promotion play-offs]] against [[Hungary national football team|Hungary]] on 14 March 2025.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.tff.org/default.aspx?pageID=202&ftxtID=47025 |title=A Millî Takımımızın Macaristan Maçları Aday Kadrosu Açıklandı |website=TFF.org |access-date=14 March 2025 |date=14 March 2025 |language=tr}}</ref>

==Style of play==
Aydın often plays as a winger, and is capable of playing on either flank, due to his ability with both feet. He is capable of cutting into the centre onto his stronger right foot from the left wing, and of creating chances and providing assists for teammates from the right thanks to his vision. He is also able to play in the centre as a second striker, due to his composure, clinical finishing, and eye for goal.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Hürriyet|url=https://www.hurriyet.com.tr/sporarena/oguz-aydindan-itiraf-ve-euro-2024-iddiasi-ruya-gibi-bir-olaydi-sampiyon-olabiliriz-42452930|title=Oğuz Aydın'dan itiraf ve EURO 2024 iddiası: 'Rüya gibi bir olaydı, şampiyon olabiliriz'|date=14 May 2024|access-date=3 December 2024}}</ref>

